The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Sonalika growth plans

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 New Delhi, June 14: Utility vehicle and farm equipment maker Sonalika Group today launched an upgraded version of its multi-utility vehicle Rhino Rx and unveiled plans to invest Rs 1,150 crore over the next three years to expand operations.

 The new variant would be priced between Rs 5.85 lakh and Rs 6.95 lakh (ex-showroom Delhi). The group also plans to launch a sports utility vehicle by 2010. It will invest through two subsidiaries, International Cars and Motors (ICML) and International Tractors (ITL).

 ICML will invest around Rs 700 crore by 2009 to expand capacity and develop a sports utility vehicle. ITL will invest about Rs 450 crore to set up a tractor making unit in the south and raise the capacity at Hoshiarpur unit in Punjab. We are looking at setting up a greenfield plant in the south and have already written to the governments of Tamil Nadu, Andhra Pradesh and Karnataka, said L.D. Mittal, chairman, Sonalika Group. 




